<ce:para>In this paper we consider multistage stochastic programs with endogenous parameters where investment strategies are considered to reduce uncertainty, and time-varying distributions are used to describe uncertainty. We present the proposed ideas in the context of the planning of process networks with uncertain yields. We propose a new mixed-integer/disjunctive programming mdoel which is reformulated as a mixed-integer linear program. The model can be solved, through an LP-based branch and bound for smaller instances or with a duality-based branch and bound for larger problems. Â© 2006 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.</ce:para>
